Histogramas en un solo gráfico vs densidad y normal

GRÁFICO N°2

histDenNorm <- function (dataset, ...) {
          hist(dataset, ...) # Histograma
          lines(density(dataset), col = "blue", lwd = 2) # Densidad
          x2 <- seq(min(dataset), max(dataset), length = 60)
          f <- dnorm(x2, mean(dataset), sd(dataset))
          lines(x2, f, col = "red", lwd = 2) # Normal
        
        }
        
        par(mfrow = c(3, 4))
        
        histDenNorm(dataset$blancos, prob = TRUE, xlab="", ylab = "", main = "Blancos", freq = FALSE, col = cm.colors(30))
        
        histDenNorm(dataset$negros, prob = TRUE,xlab="", ylab = "", main = "Afroamericanos",freq = FALSE, col = cm.colors(30))
        
        histDenNorm(dataset$nativos, prob = TRUE,xlab="", ylab = "", main = "Nativos",freq = FALSE, col = cm.colors(30))
        
        histDenNorm(dataset$asiaticos, prob = TRUE,xlab="", ylab = "", main = "Asiáticos",freq = FALSE, col = cm.colors(30))
        
        histDenNorm(dataset$hispanicos, prob = TRUE,xlab="", ylab = "", main = "Hispanos/Latinos",freq = FALSE, col = cm.colors(30))
        
        histDenNorm(dataset$income, prob = TRUE,xlab="", ylab = "", main = "Nivel de Ingresos",freq = FALSE, col = cm.colors(30))
        
        histDenNorm(dataset$pov, prob = TRUE,xlab="", ylab = "", main = "Tasa de Pobreza",freq = FALSE, col = cm.colors(30))
        
        histDenNorm(dataset$urate, prob = TRUE,xlab="", ylab = "", main = "Tasa de Desempleo",freq = FALSE, col = cm.colors(30))
        
        histDenNorm(dataset$college, prob = TRUE,xlab="", ylab = "", main = "Educación",freq = FALSE, col = cm.colors(30))
        
        histDenNorm(dataset$`Death in custody`, prob = TRUE,xlab="", ylab = "", main = "Muerte Bajo Custodia",freq = FALSE, col = cm.colors(30))
        
        histDenNorm(dataset$Gunshot, prob = TRUE,xlab="", ylab = "", main = "Muerte por Disparo",freq = FALSE, col = cm.colors(30))
        
        histDenNorm(dataset$`Struck by vehicle`, prob = TRUE,xlab="", ylab = "", main = "Muerte Golpeado por vehículo",freq = FALSE, col = cm.colors(30))

par(mfrow = c(1, 1))

Corremos el modelo de K-means

set.seed(1234)
        model <- kmeans(
          pca$li,
          centers = 4,
          iter.max = 400,
          nstart = 300,
          algorithm = "Forgy"
        )

Imprimimos la silueta

silhouette(model$cluster, dist(pca$li)) %>% 
          plot()

Asignamos la variable de cluster en nuestro dataset

output <- mutate(dataset, cluster = as.double(model$cluster))

Observamos el clustering

d2 <- output %>%
          dplyr::select(2:10,cluster)
        
        d2f <- scale(d2)
        
        fviz_cluster(object = model,
                     data = d2f,
                     show.clust.cent = TRUE,
                     ellipse.type = "euclid",
                     star.plot = TRUE,
                     repel = TRUE,
                     pointsize = 0.5,
                     outlier.color = "darkred") +
          labs(title = "Resultados de Clustering K-means") +
          theme_bw() +
          theme(plot.title = element_text(face = "bold",
                                          hjust = 0.5,
                                          size = 13),
